      {
        "id": 3303240,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-12-28T12:37:14.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I actually already visited, Herwig! And I agree with you. Vineyards are all organic certified (they were rented to someone who worked organically and Benoit continued). Winemaking is simple but attentive: destemmed, classic macerations in concrete tanks, basket press, 18 months in barrel. 2019 is the first real vintage (Benoit made a few barrels for the preceding decade which he mainly sold at wine fairs), and a very strong start as you say.</p>",
        "post_number": 9,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-04T10:51:41.095Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
