        "created_at": "2021-12-28T14:21:20.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"173068\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>I actually already visited, Herwig! And I agree with you. Vineyards are all organic certified (they were rented to someone who worked organically and Benoit continued). Winemaking is simple but attentive: destemmed, classic macerations in concrete tanks, basket press, 18 months in barrel. 2019 is the first real vintage (Benoit made a few barrels for the preceding decade which he mainly sold at wine fairs), and a very strong start as you say.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thanks\u2026William - as usual  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\"></p>",
